      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. so basically they're saying it keeps things fair and objective. i've heard some people say originalism is just a way for certain judges to push a specific political agenda though. is there a way to tell if someone is actually using originalism for its intended purpose or if they're just using it as a cover for their own views?",
