    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i see. so it's all about the methodology then. but some people argue that because history can be interpreted in so many ways, originalism is basically just a \"living\" interpretation but with more homework. do you think originalism is actually a valid, scholarly way to look at the law, or is it just a legal tactic used to justify conservative outcomes in modern court cases?",
